4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE CHILD CARE WORKFORCE
5 RECRUITMENT AND RETENTION SUPPORT PAYMENT PROGRAM; PROVIDING ELIGIBLE USES FOR
6 WHICH THE SUPPORT PAYMENTS MAY BE SPENT; PROVIDING A METHOD FOR DISTRIBUTION OF
7 FUNDS; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; PROVIDING AN APPROPRIATION; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE
8 DATE.”
9
10 WHEREAS, Montana's early childhood care and education industry provides a service essential to the
11 robust engagement of the broader workforce of the state by making it possible for parents of young children to
12 be employed; and
13 WHEREAS, persistent low wages in child-care jobs have significantly hampered recruitment and
14 retention of the child-care workforce, impacting the sector's ability to provide reliable, safe, and sufficient care to
15 Montana's communities; and
16 WHEREAS, raising prices for child care creates a cost burden on families that leads to parents leaving
17 the workforce.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Child care workforce recruitment and retention support payment
22 program -- purpose. (1) There is a child care workforce recruitment and retention support payment program
23 administered by the department of public health and human services.
24 (2) The purpose of the program is to provide payments to eligible child-care facilities to use the
25 funds to strengthen the ability of providers to recruit and retain qualified child-care workers.
26
27 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. For the purposes of [sections 1 through 5], the following
28 definitions apply:
- 1 - Authorized Print Version – ****

