1 (1) "Child-care worker" means a person who is listed on the early childhood project workforce
2 registry who owns or is employed by an eligible licensed day-care center, registered group day-care home, or
3 registered family day-care home.
4 (2) "Eligible child-care facility" means a licensed day-care center, registered family day-care home,
5 or registered group day-care home.
6
7 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Eligible use of funds -- day-care centers and group day-care homes.
8 A licensed day-care center or a registered group day-care home that receives support payments pursuant to
9 [sections 1 through 5] may only spend the funds on personnel costs. A licensed day-care center or registered
10 group day-care home may spend the funds on the following eligible uses for the benefit of child-care workers
11 employed at the center:
12 (1) to supplement the wages paid;
13 (2) to offset the cost or pay directly for the benefits provided;
14 (3) to provide a signing bonus for a newly hired child-care worker; and
15 (4) to provide longevity bonuses to recognize employees who have remained with a single day-
16 care center or group day-care home.
17
18 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Eligible use of funds -- family day-care homes. A registered family
19 day-care home that receives support payments pursuant to [sections 1 through 5] may only spend the funds on
20 the following eligible uses:
21 (1) for the benefit of child-care workers employed at the family day-care home:
22 (a) to supplement the wages paid;
23 (b) to offset the cost or pay directly for the benefits provided;
24 (c) to provide a signing bonus for a newly hired child-care worker; and
25 (d) to provide longevity bonuses to recognize employees who have remained with a single family
26 day-care home;
27 (2) facility costs of the family day-care home;
28 (3) equipment for the family day-care home;
- 2 - Authorized Print Version – ****

