1 (4) professional development for the child-care workers; or
2 (5) mental health support for the children in care at the family day-care home.
3
4 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Distribution of funds. (1) The department shall distribute the support
5 payments on a monthly basis to eligible child-care facilities in an amount proportional to the number of child-
6 care workers employed on a full-time or part-time basis.
7 (2) For the purposes of this section, a full-time employee is an employee who works 40 hours a
8 week.
9
10 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Appropriation. (1) The following money is appropriated from the general
11 fund to the department of public health and human services for the purposes of the child care workforce
12 recruitment and retention support payment program provided for in [sections 1 through 5]:
13 Fiscal year beginning July 1, 2025 $59,900,000
14 Fiscal year beginning July 1, 2026 $59,900,000
15 (2) The funds appropriated may only be spent for the eligible uses of funds as provided in
16 [sections 3 and 4].
17 (3) The legislature intends that the appropriation in this section be considered part of the ongoing
18 base for the next legislative session.
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 7. Codification instruction. [Sections 1 through 5] are intended to be
21 codified as an integral part of Title 52, chapter 2, part 7, and the provisions of Title 52, chapter 2, part 7, apply
22 to [sections 1 through 5].
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
